y, St. Denis arrived in Paris as its first bishop -- one of seven others sent to evangelize present-day France.\", \"from\": 263, \"to\": 397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 293, \"end\": 298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.859097945388085e-41, \"text\": \"Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 310, \"end\": 315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0443744791793403e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 390, \"end\": 396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9995473462363018, \"rank\": 0.0004504849372768246, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the mid-third century\", \"from\": 266, \"to\": 287}, {\"ngram\": \"its first bishop\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 335}, {\"ngram\": \"seven others\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 358}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He subsequently was martyred, along with two companions, Eleutherius and Rusticus, by suffering decapitation, presumably a result of the persecution of the Emperor Decius.\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 562, \"end\": 568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Decius\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.29944950372442e-48, \"text\": \"Decius\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Decius\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Decius\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two companions\", \"from\": 439, \"to\": 453}, {\"ngram\": \"Eleutherius\", \"from\": 455, \"to\": 466}, {\"ngram\": \"Rusticus\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 479}, {\"ngram\": \"decapitation\", \"from\": 494, \"to\": 506}, {\"ngram\": \"the persecution\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 546}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After his head was severed, according to legend, St. Denis carried it several miles, all the while preaching a message of repentance.\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 623, \"end\": 628, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.859097945388085e-41, \"text\": \"Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his head\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 584}, {\"ngram\": \"legend\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 617}, {\"ngram\": \"a message\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 688}, {\"ngram\": \"repentance\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 702}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Parisian pilgrim's path was popularized in the Middle Ages, visiting various sites associated with St. Denis' arrest, trial, suffering and death.\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 809, \"end\": 814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.859097945388085e-41, \"text\": \"Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A Parisian pilgrim's path\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 729}, {\"ngram\": \"the Middle Ages\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 764}, {\"ngram\": \"various sites\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 788}, {\"ngram\": \"trial\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 829}, {\"ngram\": \"suffering\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 850}]}, {\"sentence\": \"St. Genevieve later saw to the construction of a church on the site of St. Denis' tomb, the site of the present-day cathedral bearing his name just north of Paris.\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 1015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 927, \"end\": 932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.859097945388085e-41, \"text\": \"Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Denis_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1009, \"end\": 1014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0443744791793403e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"St. Genevieve\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 865}, {\"ngram\": \"the construction\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"a church\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 907}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 919}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"his name\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 994}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And he's spotted on the facade of Notre Dame Cathedral, just near the main entrance.\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1100, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the facade\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1046}, {\"ngram\": \"Notre Dame Cathedral\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1070}, {\"ngram\": \"the main entrance\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1099}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His feast is Oct. 9.\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1121, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His feast\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1110}, {\"ngram\": \"Oct.\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1118}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even as a 7-year-old girl, St. Genevieve wanted to live a life consecrated to God alone.\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1154, \"end\": 1163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.379020679538821e-60, \"text\": \"Genevieve\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a 7-year-old girl\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1148}, {\"ngram\": \"a life\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1185}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1204}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This desire was encouraged when she met St. Germain of Auxerre, a holy bishop.\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1290, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This desire\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1223}, {\"ngram\": \"St. Germain\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1263}, {\"ngram\": \"Auxerre\", \"from\": 1267, \"to\": 1274}, {\"ngram\": \"a holy bishop\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1289}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having moved to the city from her peasant home in the countryside outside of Paris, Genevieve quickly became associated with the extraordinary and miraculous.\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1449, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1368, \"end\": 1373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0443744791793403e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1375, \"end\": 1384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.379020679538821e-60, \"text\": \"Genevieve\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1315}, {\"ngram\": \"her peasant home\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1337}, {\"ngram\": \"the countryside\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1356}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her intercession with God brought about healings and protection in life and death, and she was soon considered to be a visionary and a mystic.\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1592, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her intercession\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1466}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 1472, \"to\": 1475}, {\"ngram\": \"healings\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1498}, {\"ngram\": \"protection\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1513}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 1517, \"to\": 1521}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 1526, \"to\": 1531}, {\"ngram\": \"a visionary\", \"from\": 1567, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"a mystic\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1591}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the help of her prayers and with her ability to evangelize amid crises, St. Genevieve is credited with having saved Paris from invaders and destruction on multiple occasions.\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1672, \"end\": 1681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.379020679538821e-60, \"text\": \"Genevieve\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\"}, {\"begin\": 1712, \"end\": 1717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0443744791793403e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the help\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1604}, {\"ngram\": \"her prayers\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1619}, {\"ngram\": \"her ability\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1640}, {\"ngram\": \"crises\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1666}, {\"ngram\": \"invaders\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1731}, {\"ngram\": \"destruction\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1747}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple occasions\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1769}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Around the turn of the sixth century, St. Genevieve was instrumental in the conversion of the first Catholic king of France, Clovis I.\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1905, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1813, \"end\": 1822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.379020679538821e-60, \"text\": \"Genevieve\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\"}, {\"begin\": 1871, \"end\": 1879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2079900418148573e-32, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1888, \"end\": 1894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9995473462363018, \"rank\": 0.0004504849372768246, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the turn\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1786}, {\"ngram\": \"the sixth century\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"the conversion\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1857}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Through the centuries following her death around 500, Genevieve's relics were often venerated and processed publicly amid great trials facing Parisians.\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 2058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1960, \"end\": 1969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.379020679538821e-60, \"text\": \"Genevieve\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Genevieve\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the centuries\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 1927}, {\"ngram\": \"her death\", \"from\": 1938, \"to\": 1947}, {\"ngram\": \"great trials\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2040}, {\"ngram\": \"Parisians\", \"from\": 2048, \"to\": 2057}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her relics were subsequently destroyed during the French Revolution, although a few small remaining pieces survived and are preserved in Paris' parish church of St. \\u00c9tienne-du-Mont.\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2196, \"end\": 2201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0443744791793403e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her relics\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2069}, {\"ngram\": \"the French Revolution\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2126}, {\"ngram\": \"a few small remaining pieces\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2165}, {\"ngram\": \"St. \\u00c9tienne\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2231}, {\"ngram\": \"du\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2234}, {\"ngram\": \"Mont.\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her feast is Jan. 3.\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2261, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her feast\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2250}, {\"ngram\": \"Jan.\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2258}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The reign of St. Louis IX as king of France, in the middle half of the 13th century, was marked as a golden age of French culture and prominence on the global stage.\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2300, \"end\": 2306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9995473462363018, \"rank\": 0.0004504849372768246, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2378, \"end\": 2392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The reign\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2272}, {\"ngram\": \"St. Louis IX\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2288}, {\"ngram\": \"king\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2296}, {\"ngram\": \"the middle half\", \"from\": 2311, \"to\": 2326}, {\"ngram\": \"the 13th century\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2346}, {\"ngram\": \"a golden age\", \"from\": 2362, \"to\": 2374}, {\"ngram\": \"prominence\", \"from\": 2397, \"to\": 2407}, {\"ngram\": \"the global stage\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2427}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A man of courage and action, he also supported the intellectual life of the church and supported the establishment of a theological school in Paris that would be later known as the Sorbonne.\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2571, \"end\": 2576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0443744791793403e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"courage\", \"from\": 2438, \"to\": 2445}, {\"ngram\": \"action\", \"from\": 2450, \"to\": 2456}, {\"ngram\": \"the intellectual life\", \"from\": 2476, \"to\": 2497}, {\"ngram\": \"the church\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2511}, {\"ngram\": \"the establishment\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2543}, {\"ngram\": \"a theological school\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2567}, {\"ngram\": \"the Sorbonne\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2618}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He even was joined once at court by the great St. Thomas Aquinas, a preeminent theologian and philosopher of the day.\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2737, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"court\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2652}, {\"ngram\": \"the great St. Thomas Aquinas\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2684}, {\"ngram\": \"a preeminent theologian\", \"from\": 2686, \"to\": 2709}, {\"ngram\": \"philosopher\", \"from\": 2714, \"to\": 2725}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 2729, \"to\": 2736}]}, {\"sentence\": \"St. Louis' life's highest aim was to give his all for the glory of God and the good of his people.\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2836, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"St. Louis' life's highest aim\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2767}, {\"ngram\": \"the glory\", \"from\": 2792, \"to\": 2801}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 2805, \"to\": 2808}, {\"ngram\": \"the good\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2821}, {\"ngram\": \"his people\", \"from\": 2825, \"to\": 2835}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was evident in leading two of the Crusades, at which time he took possession of a relic of Christ's crown of thorns.\", \"from\": 2837, \"to\": 2958, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2933, \"end\": 2939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.55084253197541e-14, \"text\": \"Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Crusades\", \"from\": 2872, \"to\": 2884}, {\"ngram\": \"which time\", \"from\": 2889, \"to\": 2899}, {\"ngram\": \"possession\", \"from\": 2908, \"to\": 2918}, {\"ngram\": \"a relic\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 2929}, {\"ngram\": \"thorns\", \"from\": 2951, \"to\": 2957}]}, {\"sentence\": \"St. Louis built a magnificent chapel in Paris to house the relic.\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 3024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2999, \"end\": 3004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0443744791793403e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"St. Louis\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 2968}, {\"ngram\": \"a magnificent chapel\", \"from\": 2975, \"to\": 2995}, {\"ngram\": \"the relic\", \"from\": 3014, \"to\": 3023}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Known as Sainte Chappelle, it remains one of the most visited places in France.\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3097, \"end\": 3103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9995473462363018, \"rank\": 0.0004504849372768246, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sainte Chappelle\", \"from\": 3034, \"to\": 3050}, {\"ngram\": \"the most visited places\", \"from\": 3070, \"to\": 3093}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He died in 1270 in Tunisia after contracting dysentery en route to the Holy Land during the eighth Crusade.\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3124, \"end\": 3131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia\", \"score\": 0.9999967301499764, \"rank\": 2.9286190692611185e-06, \"text\": \"Tunisia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"dysentery\", \"from\": 3150, \"to\": 3159}, {\"ngram\": \"route\", \"from\": 3163, \"to\": 3168}, {\"ngram\": \"the Holy Land\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3185}, {\"ngram\": \"the eighth Crusade\", \"from\": 3193, \"to\": 3211}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His feast is Aug. 25.\", \"from\": 3213, \"to\": 3234, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His feast\", \"from\": 3213, \"to\": 3222}, {\"ngram\": \"Aug.\", \"from\": 3226, \"to\": 3230}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ordained a priest in 1600, St. Vincent de Paul came to see clearly how holy priests were needed to reform the church besieged by clericalism and corruption.\", \"from\": 3236, \"to\": 3392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3267, \"end\": 3274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0925136154326724e-26, \"text\": \"Vincent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a priest\", \"from\": 3245, \"to\": 3253}, {\"ngram\": \"how holy priests\", \"from\": 3303, \"to\": 3319}, {\"ngram\": \"the church\", \"from\": 3342, \"to\": 3352}, {\"ngram\": \"clericalism\", \"from\": 3365, \"to\": 3376}, {\"ngram\": \"corruption\", \"from\": 3381, \"to\": 3391}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is nothing so grand as a good priest,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3393, \"to\": 3447, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 3403, \"to\": 3410}, {\"ngram\": \"a good priest\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3436}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As he poured out his life in ministry for others, especially those on the margins, he desired to assist the church in renewing priestly life with a focus on personal sanctification and the needs of the poor.\", \"from\": 3448, \"to\": 3655, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his life\", \"from\": 3465, \"to\": 3473}, {\"ngram\": \"ministry\", \"from\": 3477, \"to\": 3485}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 3490, \"to\": 3496}, {\"ngram\": \"especially those\", \"from\": 3498, \"to\": 3514}, {\"ngram\": \"the margins\", \"from\": 3518, \"to\": 3529}, {\"ngram\": \"the church\", \"from\": 3552, \"to\": 3562}, {\"ngram\": \"priestly life\", \"from\": 3575, \"to\": 3588}, {\"ngram\": \"a focus\", \"from\": 3594, \"to\": 3601}, {\"ngram\": \"personal sanctification\", \"from\": 3605, \"to\": 3628}, {\"ngram\": \"the needs\", \"from\": 3633, \"to\": 3642}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With that in mind, Vincent established the Congregation of the Mission -- a men's order also known as the Vincentians, directed toward those abandoned and forgotten -- in addition to working for seminary reform and founding the Daughters of Charity so that women could share in ministry to the sick and poor.\", \"from\": 3656, \"to\": 3964, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3675, \"end\": 3682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0925136154326724e-26, \"text\": \"Vincent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\"}, {\"begin\": 3762, \"end\": 3773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_de_Paul\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.878009842518227e-31, \"text\": \"Vincentians\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_de_Paul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_de_Paul\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"mind\", \"from\": 3669, \"to\": 3673}, {\"ngram\": \"the Congregation\", \"from\": 3695, \"to\": 3711}, {\"ngram\": \"the Mission\", \"from\": 3715, \"to\": 3726}, {\"ngram\": \"a men's order\", \"from\": 3730, \"to\": 3743}, {\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 3827, \"to\": 3835}, {\"ngram\": \"seminary reform\", \"from\": 3851, \"to\": 3866}, {\"ngram\": \"the Daughters\", \"from\": 3880, \"to\": 3893}, {\"ngram\": \"Charity\", \"from\": 3897, \"to\": 3904}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 3913, \"to\": 3918}, {\"ngram\": \"ministry\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 3942}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vincent de Paul died in Paris in 1660, heralded as having \\\"changed the face of the Church.\\\"\", \"from\": 3965, \"to\": 4056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3965, \"end\": 3972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0925136154326724e-26, \"text\": \"Vincent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\"}, {\"begin\": 3989, \"end\": 3994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0443744791793403e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the face\", \"from\": 4032, \"to\": 4040}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 4044, \"to\": 4054}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His feast is Sept. 27.\", \"from\": 4057, \"to\": 4079, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His feast\", \"from\": 4057, \"to\": 4066}, {\"ngram\": \"Sept.\", \"from\": 4070, \"to\": 4075}]}, {\"sentence\": \"St. Louise de Marillac grew up in a home without stability -- she was born out of wedlock, was not afforded the rights of other siblings and was mistreated by her father's wife.\", \"from\": 4081, \"to\": 4258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4085, \"end\": 4103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_de_Marillac\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Louise de Marillac\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_de_Marillac\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_de_Marillac\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a home\", \"from\": 4115, \"to\": 4121}, {\"ngram\": \"stability\", \"from\": 4130, \"to\": 4139}, {\"ngram\": \"wedlock\", \"from\": 4163, \"to\": 4170}, {\"ngram\": \"the rights\", \"from\": 4189, \"to\": 4199}, {\"ngram\": \"other siblings\", \"from\": 4203, \"to\": 4217}, {\"ngram\": \"her father's wife\", \"from\": 4240, \"to\": 4257}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still a member of an affluent family, Louise received an education at a convent school sponsored by royalty outside of Paris.\", \"from\": 4259, \"to\": 4384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4297, \"end\": 4303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\", \"score\": 0.9999999998699423, \"rank\": 1.2987637779847976e-10, \"text\": \"Louise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\"}, {\"begin\": 4378, \"end\": 4383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0443744791793403e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an affluent family\", \"from\": 4277, \"to\": 4295}, {\"ngram\": \"an education\", \"from\": 4313, \"to\": 4325}, {\"ngram\": \"a convent school\", \"from\": 4329, \"to\": 4345}, {\"ngram\": \"royalty\", \"from\": 4359, \"to\": 4366}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although drawn initially to religious life, Louise was denied entrance to a convent.\", \"from\": 4385, \"to\": 4469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4429, \"end\": 4435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\", \"score\": 0.9999999998699423, \"rank\": 1.2987637779847976e-10, \"text\": \"Louise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"religious life\", \"from\": 4413, \"to\": 4427}, {\"ngram\": \"entrance\", \"from\": 4447, \"to\": 4455}, {\"ngram\": \"a convent\", \"from\": 4459, \"to\": 4468}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At a loss for what to do, it was arranged for her to marry the queen's secretary Antoine Le Gras in 1613.\", \"from\": 4470, \"to\": 4575, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a loss\", \"from\": 4473, \"to\": 4479}, {\"ngram\": \"the queen's secretary\", \"from\": 4529, \"to\": 4550}, {\"ngram\": \"Antoine Le Gras\", \"from\": 4551, \"to\": 4566}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Looking to give more of her life to service to the poor and sickly, Louise was instrumental in forming the Ladies of Charity, an association of the wives of wealthy men.\", \"from\": 4576, \"to\": 4745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4644, \"end\": 4650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\", \"score\": 0.9999999998699423, \"rank\": 1.2987637779847976e-10, \"text\": \"Louise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her life\", \"from\": 4600, \"to\": 4608}, {\"ngram\": \"the Ladies\", \"from\": 4679, \"to\": 4689}, {\"ngram\": \"Charity\", \"from\": 4693, \"to\": 4700}, {\"ngram\": \"an association\", \"from\": 4702, \"to\": 4716}, {\"ngram\": \"the wives\", \"from\": 4720, \"to\": 4729}, {\"ngram\": \"wealthy men\", \"from\": 4733, \"to\": 4744}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This eventually paved the way for the Daughters of Charity, which Louise helped establish with St. Vincent de Paul after she was widowed in 1625 and in which she professed religious vows.\", \"from\": 4746, \"to\": 4933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4812, \"end\": 4818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\", \"score\": 0.9999999998699423, \"rank\": 1.2987637779847976e-10, \"text\": \"Louise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\"}, {\"begin\": 4845, \"end\": 4852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0925136154326724e-26, \"text\": \"Vincent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 4768, \"to\": 4775}, {\"ngram\": \"the Daughters\", \"from\": 4780, \"to\": 4793}, {\"ngram\": \"Charity\", \"from\": 4797, \"to\": 4804}, {\"ngram\": \"religious vows\", \"from\": 4918, \"to\": 4932}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Considered a patron of the church's charitable services, Louise died in 1660 and was canonized three centuries later.\", \"from\": 4934, \"to\": 5051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4991, \"end\": 4997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\", \"score\": 0.9999999998699423, \"rank\": 1.2987637779847976e-10, \"text\": \"Louise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louise_of_Mecklenburg-Strelitz\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a patron\", \"from\": 4945, \"to\": 4953}, {\"ngram\": \"the church's charitable services\", \"from\": 4957, \"to\": 4989}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her feast is March 15.\", \"from\": 5052, \"to\": 5074, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her feast\", \"from\": 5052, \"to\": 5061}, {\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 5065, \"to\": 5070}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Born into an agrarian family, the ninth of 11 children, St. Catherine Laboure desired religious life from an early age.\", \"from\": 5076, \"to\": 5195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5089, \"end\": 5097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agrarian_society\", \"score\": 0.907446385227499, \"rank\": 0.09601789613896805, \"text\": \"agrarian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agrarian_society\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agrarian_society\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"11 children\", \"from\": 5119, \"to\": 5130}, {\"ngram\": \"St. Catherine Laboure\", \"from\": 5132, \"to\": 5153}, {\"ngram\": \"religious life\", \"from\": 5162, \"to\": 5176}, {\"ngram\": \"an early age\", \"from\": 5182, \"to\": 5194}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And despite her father's resistance, she eventually joined the Daughters of Charity in Paris in 1830.\", \"from\": 5196, \"to\": 5297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5283, \"end\": 5288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0443744791793403e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her father's resistance\", \"from\": 5208, \"to\": 5231}, {\"ngram\": \"the Daughters\", \"from\": 5255, \"to\": 5268}, {\"ngram\": \"Charity\", \"from\": 5272, \"to\": 5279}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her desire to serve the needy led to decades of care for the poor, sick and elderly.\", \"from\": 5298, \"to\": 5382, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her desire\", \"from\": 5298, \"to\": 5308}, {\"ngram\": \"decades\", \"from\": 5335, \"to\": 5342}, {\"ngram\": \"care\", \"from\": 5346, \"to\": 5350}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During those decades she remained in hidden silence regarding what makes her most well-known today -- namely, supernatural visions she received from the Blessed Virgin Mary.\", \"from\": 5383, \"to\": 5556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5536, \"end\": 5555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999880137694, \"rank\": 1.1985969736889937e-08, \"text\": \"Blessed Virgin Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those decades\", \"from\": 5390, \"to\": 5403}, {\"ngram\": \"hidden silence\", \"from\": 5420, \"to\": 5434}, {\"ngram\": \"namely, supernatural visions\", \"from\": 5485, \"to\": 5513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These visions began just months after St. Catherine started her novitiate o